Program: Discovery
Title: The Living Universe and Cosmology
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxtc
Last Broadcast Date: 15 May 2001
A history of cosmology, commentators include the physicist Paul Davies. Cosmology presents differing views of the universe and how it began, today the computer is able to help cosmologists with their research. When it comes to cosmology one thing has remained, the universe as having a purpose.